main event: An unidentified flying object (UFO) was observed in Winterset, Iowa on 10 January 1955 at 21:07 GMT. The object was described as a white light varying in intensity and was seen at various altitudes, engaging in high-speed and erratic maneuvers. The sighting lasted for 25 seconds and the object made a head-on pass with the observer's aircraft.
interesting points: The UFO was observed by credible witnesses, including the Observations Officer for the 8th Fighter Bomber Squadron, Operations Officer and a Major from the Iowa Air National Guard.
The object's maneuverability and speed made it difficult for the observer aircraft to establish radar contact or to maneuver close to the UFO.
The report suggests that the UFO exhibited understanding of tactical maneuvers and used occasional acceleration in an erratic manner.
The sighting officer had no logical explanation for the observed phenomena.
The object was seen engaging in rapid climbing movements, going from 20,000 feet to 30,000 feet in a short amount of time.
witnesses: Observations Officer for the 8th Fighter Bomber Squadron, Operations Officer and a Major from the Iowa Air National Guard
